commit 9cc72b517b253657c2ce587e984e477d7f0afd6a
Author: GoldenGnu <GoldenGnu@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Wed May 18 13:29:35 2022 +0200

    Code: Optimized stockpile: New/Clone/Delete/Import/Hide/Show
    Moved stockpileIDs to a SQLite database, with a table for each profile.
    Now keep track of hidden stockpiles, instead of shown.
    That makes New/Clone/Delete/Import shown by default and therefor have zero cost.
    Hiding/showing stockpiles and deleting/renaming a profile is the only operations with a cost (Cost with SQLite much lower than saving the entire profile).

Author: GoldenGnu <GoldenGnu@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Sun Jun 6 12:18:34 2021 +0200

    As complete a restore at relaunch as possible #216 (#248)
    
    * New Feature: Save blank filters, ie those with no text. (Issue #216)
    
    * New Feature: Save blank filter enabled state. Update filter import and export to include enabled state. (Issue #216)
    
    * New Feature: Save current working table filters as they change and restore them on startup. (Issue #216)
    
    * New Feature: Save current state of filter panel display (shown/hidden) as it changes and restore them on startup. (Issue #216)
    
    * New Feature: Make enabled state in import and export human readable. (Issue #216)
    
    * New Feature: Change export data format in settings file in order to support saving all values per table instead of having most of them shared across all exports. (Issue #216)
    
    * New Feature: Add filter and column selection radios to what is saved from export dialog. Also add the selected views or filters and add logic to handle if they are deleted.  (Issue #216)
    
    * New Feature: Separate data load from UI logic as much as possible for export dialog. (Issue #216)
    
    * New Feature: Add additional settings from the TrackerTab to the settings file and add logic to save and load them. Includes shown trackers, include zero, date ranges, and linear or logarithmic. (Issue #216)
    
    * New Feature: Remove unused imports from ExportSettings.java. (Issue #216)
    
    * Refactor: Move tracker settings from Settings.java into the new TrackerSettings.java
    
    * PR Review: Changes from PR review of PR 248.
    
    * PR Review: More changes from PR review of PR 248.

Author: tryfan <na@na.com>
Date:   Sat Aug 7 16:00:31 2010 +0000

    Made changes in the constructor to allow the resizing of the window.  Intended behaviour is to allow the window to expand in both width and height but not allow the window to shrink smaller than the existing default size.
    
    Other changes to existing components within the frame ensure they resize accordingly.
    
    I'm not completely happy with the change however, the window can still be shrunk slightly after display, which isn't intended.  This means that the gap at the bottom and the right of the frame aren't maintained.  While not a show-stopper, it is slightly annoying!

commit f7acf204b704200ca3baa753bee5cf987fdc3430
Author: Flaming Candle <na@na.com>
Date:   Fri May 14 15:28:13 2010 +0000

    Fixed the issue 85, where the brute force algorithm was returning worse routes then the nearest neighbour. This was caused by returning the distance of the last investigated route rather then the distance of the shortest route. The route that was returned was in fact correct, just the distance reported was incorrect. (If you add up the distance of the route, it was not equal to the displayed distance)
    
    Bumped the routing version to 1.0.1 and added a few tests for the routing bug.

commit 09ed7a14d8ef2c0325431487d08ceabfd8b7df8c
Author: Flaming Candle <na@na.com>
Date:   Thu May 13 11:20:02 2010 +0000

    Right. How many files can I touch in a single (non-white-space) commit?
    
    Converted the logging to use SLF4J rather then the custom logging framework.
    Added no-more-commons-logging and the jcl-to-slf4j adaptor to ensure that all logging events are passed to the configured logging framework (currently log4j)
    
    Log4j is added as a runtime dependency, and it should stay there. configuration is done through the log4j.properties and various system properties (log.home and log.level) that can be specified on the command line if needed: e.g.
    java -Dlog.home=/foo/bar/ -jar jeveassets.jar
